footer: footer.title: {[TimesNewRoman x 9]}{[6.502 x 6, 4.71 x 3]}{[normal x 9]}{[null x 9]} //The interval between adjacent waves was 1 year except that of wave 5 and wave 6. The average interval between wave 5 and wave 6 was 10 months, since 12th graders needed to sit for the public examination. ^{a} The numbers of participants who completed six, five, four, three, two, and one assessments were 2,023, 472, 242, 200, 179, and 212. ^{b} The seven response levels were combined into three categories. ^{c} Confrmatory factor analyses showed that these items loaded on the target constructs (emotional: l’s > .63; social: l’s > .81; moral: l’s > .61), and the measurement models of three constructs fitted the data well across the six waves, CFIs > .970, TLIs > .95, RMSEAs < .06.
